This repository has no license yet. Until a LICENSE is selected and
committed, default copyright applies: no permission is granted to use,
copy, modify, or distribute this code.

Pick deliberately before any public push. The open-core split makes this
a business/legal decision, not a default:

  - Apache-2.0 / MIT  — maximal adoption; anyone (incl. competitors) may
    host the engine. Fine if the moat is the closed control plane.
  - Source-available (BSL / Elastic / SSPL-style) — adoption with a
    hosting carve-out. Choose if "anyone may resell the engine as a
    service" is an actual threat.

Do not treat this as legal advice. Decide, then replace this file.
